[[Cairo]] has been at the epicentre of much of the crisis. Most of the protests were held in downtown [[Tahrir Square]]. On the first three days of the protests, there were clashes between the central security police and protesters and as of 28 January, police forces withdrew from most of Cairo. Citizens then formed neighbourhood watch groups to keep the order as widespread looting was reported.
